comments: DeRozan (CHI) places his forearm to Matthews' (MIL) back underneath the basket and makes marginal contact as they pursue the loose ball.
Holiday (MIL) places his forearm to DeRozan's (CHI) front defending his drive and marginal contact occurs.
Vucevic (CHI) establishes himself in a screening position in Middleton's (MIL) path and makes marginal contact to his side as they disengage.

Lopez (MIL) moves alongside of LaVine's (CHI) path to the basket and places a hand on his back but the contact is marginal.  LaVine then jumps into Lopez, who absorbs the body contact before making contact with the ball.
Lopez (MIL) makes marginal contact with Vucevic's (CHI) body off ball that does not affect his ability to get to the pass.
Lopez (MIL) establishes himself in a screening position in LaVine's (CHI) path and makes marginal contact as they disengage.
As Williams (CHI) attempts to firm up in a legal guarding position, he slides over and initiates contact across Lopez's (MIL) arms that affects his shot attempt near the rim.
Williams (CHI) and Portis (MIL) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Williams (CHI) establishes himself in a screening position in Matthews' (MIL) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
Vucevic (CHI) establishes himself in a screening position in Holiday's (MIL) path and does not deliver contact.
Portis (MIL) makes marginal contact with Vucevic's (CHI) body after the release of his shot attempt at the basket.
Lopez (MIL) places his arm against Vucevic's (CHI) body after the release of his putback and the contact is marginal.
Lopez (MIL) establishes himself in a screening position in LaVine's (CHI) path and makes marginal contact as he releases away from the contact.
DeRozan (CHI) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Lopez (MIL) goes to, not through DeRozan's (CHI) space at the end of his drive and marginal contact occurs as he releases his pass attempt.
Caruso (CHI) reaches in and initiates contact to Matthews' (MIL) arm that causes him to lose control of the ball.
Holiday (MIL) makes marginal contact with LaVine's (CHI) arm after the release of his jump shot attempt.

Portis (MIL) gathers the loose ball in the air and as he returns to the floor, Caruso (CHI) moves into his space and contact occurs to his head.  Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Caruso (CHI) commits a take foul on Holiday (MIL).
Matthews (MIL) and DeRozan (CHI) engage and disengage with one another off ball.
Williams (CHI) is already in Holiday's (MIL) path and releases away from the contact as they disengage.
Vucevic (CHI) sets the pick on Holiday (MIL) and makes marginal contact to his side as they disengage.
Matthews (MIL) maintains a legal guarding position defending DeRozan's (CHI) jump shot attempt.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) and LaVine (CHI) make incidental contact with each other while reaching for the rebound.
Caruso (CHI) commits a take foul on Middleton (MIL).
Vucevic (CHI) establishes himself in a screening position in Holiday's (MIL) path and makes marginal contact to his side as they separate.
Connaughton (MIL) engages with Williams (CHI) in the lane and the contact during the rebound is marginal.
